In England, in the seven days to 04 November, there were 210,769 new confirmed cases (372.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 October, there were 235,890 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 11% (25,121 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 09 November is 7,953,228 (14,064 cases per 100,000 population).
